Year = {{2014}},
Volume = {{73}},
Number = {{2, SI}},
Pages = {{499-515}},
Month = {{MAY}},
Abstract = {{To accurately describe the damage creep properties of marble, especially
   during the acceleration creep phase, creep testing was performed on the
   marble in the Jinping II hydropower station in China. Based on the
   experimental results, a time-dependent damage constitutive model was
   proposed in terms of fractional calculus theory and damage variables to
   describe these time-dependent damage characteristics. The time-dependent
   constitutive equations were derived for constant loading levels below
   and above the marble's long-term strength. The robustness and parameter
   sensitivity of the proposed model were analysed by utilizing data of
   creep testing. The results of the analysis showed that the proposed
   model could describe not only the attenuation and steady-state creep of
   marble but also the acceleration creep characteristics and negative
   exponential attenuation law of the yield strength over time when the
   constant loading was above the long-term strength. These are crucial to
   failure prevention during rock engineering construction and operating
   periods.}},
