   hydroelectric power, helping foster diversification on the generation
   side and enhance security of electricity supply based on local
   resources. Bioelectricity potential from sugarcane biomass is estimated
   to be in the range of 209-313 GWh for Nepal and 62-93 TWh for Brazil. In
   Nepal, the grid connected bioelectricity can provide power for operating
   industries, and support local development through rural electrification.
   In Brazil, the biomass potential can be further enhanced through a
   better utilization of the biomass in the sugar-ethanol industry to
   balance hydropower availability. This comparative study offers a
