Abstract = {{Application of numerical modeling techniques for dealing with continuum
   and discontinuum domains individually has increased rapidly and proved
   valuable in analysis of geotechnical engineering problems. This study
   aims at developing a computational framework that couples finite element
   method (FEM) and discontinuous deformation analysis (DDA) to analyze the
   slope stability in Jinping first stage hydropower station, southwestern
   China. The combined continuous-discontinuous model is able to describe
   the entire failure process. Shear strength reduction finite element
