   numerous ways. A relatively large amount of literature exists on these
   three issues, either separately or in different combinations, yet it is
   difficult to see how the three intertwine and what their macro-level
   impacts might be on sustainable development, security, and the five
   Central Asian countries. This paper aims to understand what constitutes
