   account of the underlying dynamical behavior of these systems, specially
   when the resulting probability distributions present remarkable features
   such as an algebraic tail, usually considered the footprint of
   self-organization and the existence of critical points. In this paper, 7
   years (from 2002 to 2008) of Europe's transport of electricity network
   failure events have been analyzed and the best fit for this empirical
   data probability distribution is presented. With the actual span of
   available data and although there exists a moderate support for the
   power-law model, the relatively small amount of events contained in the
   function's tail suggests that causal factors other than
