Abstract = {{The operation scheduling model in Northwest China Power System (NCPS),
   which is undergoing industry restructuring, is established. The peaking
   value of generators is identified. Two peaking cost compensation
   mechanisms for generators are proposed: the first one is based on the
   theory of cooperative game, the second one based on engineering concept.
   Some of the characteristics of the suggested game model are analyzed,
   and several methods for resolving the combinational explosion problem
   involved in the game-theoretic computation are described. Two numerical
   indices for quantifying the peaking capability of generators are
   proposed, the impacts of generator parameters, load variations, and
