   electricity and groundwater becomes elastic to tariff are
   socio-economically viable. Further, water productivity impacts of
   pricing would be highest when water is volumetrically allocated with
   rationing. Therefore, an effective power tariff policy followed by
   enforcement of volumetric water allocation could address the issue of
   efficiency, sustainability and equity ill groundwater use in India. (C)
   2003 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.}},
